cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about a novel multi-scale network architecture for image classification, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a classifier calibration module, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of residual learning is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed architecture, which is relevant to mobile and embedded vision problems (cs.MM).
